Probability
...........

   Not all spells are equally likely to happen in the game. The most
potent spells are generally very rare. This is determined by the
probability of each particular spell and the level of the spell caster.
The probability of a spell is expressed as a positive or negative
percentage. A spell with a probability of 0 never happens at all. A
spell with a probability of 99 is extremely common. Spells which have a
negative probability can only be obtained as BONUS spells, either when
a powerful object is killed in the game or when a meditation object
collapses while your wizard is inside it, and a few more cases. The
possibility of getting rarer spells increases when the spell caster
makes use of the Level spell.


@EndNode

