     store the chars in a buffer. WHY OH WHY doesn't RawDoFmt() default
     to sprintf string-storing when supplied with a NULL function
     parameter? This asm routine came straight out of the RKRM example
     listed under RawDoFmt() This should solve all the @{i}current@{ui}
     translation problems. Other translation problems will be dealt
     with later.

