     Dual Earthbind, Nonarchery, Convert, Sword of Sassenrath, Cursed
     Sword, Mount, NoMount, NoGrow, The Exorcist, Cartography,
     Alternography, Seismology, Telescope, Stone to Flesh,
     Inanimorphobiosis, Flesh to Stone, Mass Petrification, Brain Drain
     Beam, Demonic Touch Beam, Combat Drain Beam, Range Drain Beam,
     Recover Drain Beam, Lethargy Beam, Paralyzation Beam, Life Drain
     Beam, Toxicity Beam, Encumberance Beam, Sluggishness Beam.

 58. COUNTLESS other bugfixes!

 59. NUMEROUS other minor improvements!

 60. Vodka and Magic Wand now have a real graphic!

 61. 11 Custom Designed Levels! These levels are NOT random. They were
     designed in a special way by actual sadistic, depraved, evil Human
     Beings. Can you battle your way through them in less turns that
     the game designers? Can you even survive in them for more than 12
     turns? Find out how good a wizard you REALLY are.

 62. We have received complaints from AES and others about the game
     using 2 seperate screens because they typically run lots of
     programs and flip between them a lot so sometimes the screens get
     out-of-order. I have now (finally) dug up the information on
     attached (parent/child/family) screens and OS 3.0 is REALLY
     AWESOME!! OS 3.0 screen handling is vastly superior to OS 2.04!
     The use of attached screens also allows me to have as many screens
     open as I want without annoying anyone. All unused screens will be
     hidden.  This is going to be really kewl.

 63. AGA DETECTION code added. Now we can display different graphics
     depending on if the game is running on AGA or ECS.

 64. 64 bit alignment of screen memory implemented. This allows the
     entire computer to run faster when playing the game on AGA Amigas
     because the display will be running at 4x bandwidth.

 65. DEFAULTS CHANGED to start with 1 human vs 1 computer wizard + 4
     generators.

 66. SCREWEY QUIT BUG FINALLY SOLVED!!!!

 67. BUG: Vodka has no effect on Independents. NOW FIXED.

 68. BUG: Agents cast harmful spells against their friends and allies.
     Allegedly NOW FIXED.

 69. BUG: COMPUTER WIZARDS ALWAYS CAST PLASMABEAM STUPIDLY: NOW FIXED.

 70. I also modified the PlasmaBeamHandler and stupidity checking to be
     compatible with AgentCasting. DONE.

 71. WROTE a new PlasmaBeamRanking() routine so the computer wizards
     will try to cast it under the most favorable circumstances.

 72. FLAW: PlasmaBeamHandler always converts illegal coordinates into a
     cell with GetCell(). NOW FIXED.

 73. uhmmm there were major problems in the spellcasting AI...
     IsStupidCast() was assuming that the spell was being cast from the
     WIZARD's cell thus it couldn't possibly have worked with
     AgentCasting. Maybe this explains why agents cast sleep on
     friendly creatures? NOW FIXED.

 74. MAJOR BUGs in IntelligentComputerSpellSelect() and other routines.
     NOW FIXED.

 75. MAJOR BUG in IsStupidCast() All CAST_FREE spells were being
     handled all wrong. This was totally messing up the computer's
     thinking. CAST_FREE spells were routinely being regarded as
     REALLY_STUPID(-3) when in fact they were the best and most usefull
     spell possible. NOW FIXED.

 76. ADDED stupidity checking for Alternography.

 77. ExplorationMode option now on setup screen II.

 78. BUG: Patrick Hawkins reports: If the talklists file is not present
     then an alert is generated telling you it isn't there. Then the
     whole computer crashes. BUG: Kermit reports: If you don't have
     narrator.device then an alert is generated saying "Could not open
     narrator.device" then the whole computer crashes. BUG: James
     Conwell reports: If ANYTHING goes wrong in CommenceChaos(), a file
     is not found, a library can't be opened, a device is missing, etc.
     then a nice alert is generated telling you such. Then the entire
     computer ALWAYS crashes. ALL FIXED NOW.

 79. FIXED memory leaks.

 80. FIXED Semaphore bugs.

 81. PROBLEM: Casting Stone to Flesh or Inanimorphobiosis on a wall
     gives you a wall which can be moved but it can't actually attack
     anything. I changed it so that it will always be able to attack
     the living and if the inanimate object was undead then it will
     also be able to attack undeads. NOW FIXED.

 82. 11 NEW SPELLS: Brain Drain Beam, Demonic Touch Beam, Combat Drain
     Beam, Range Drain Beam, Recover Drain Beam, Lethargy Beam,
     Paralyzation Beam, Life Drain Beam, Toxicity Beam, Encumberance
     Beam, Sluggishness Beam. These spells do not affect corpses or
     scrolls. Each spell has its own AI routine.

 83. BUG! Combat, Maneuverability, Ranged Combat and Special Combat
     recovery/ poisoning don't work right!!! NOW FIXED.

 84. The holder of the Sword of Sassenrath makes his nearby friends more
     intelligent. DONE.

 85. Codex Sirconia Upgrade Several small corrections made.

 86. Problem: There is no explanation of Summoning, only of
     Subjugation. 7 new paragraphs added. NOW FIXED.

 87. Problem: There is no explanation of how the world can exist in a
     2-dimensional state and yet flying creatures can "fly" "over" other
     objects. 2 paragraphs added. NOW FIXED.

 88. Still need to come up with some sort of explanation for undeads
     and why they can't be attacked. ??? Added 1 more paragraph.

 89. NEW SECTION: "The Folly of Man" to explain generators. 10
     paragraphs.

 90. Put in all of SAI's new spell graphics into the game.



