Improvements from 2.5 to 2.6
----------------------------

  1. MUSIC is now played during spell-selection phase. I played a
     couple of test games with 6 theme songs installed and it was MUCH
     better than 0 theme songs like we've had in the past but it still
     wasn't nearly enough.

  2. The game feels MUCH more upbeat with the new music!!!!

  3. BUG: When starting a new game the colors on the HiRes part of the
     setup screen are all wrong and it is positioned wrong too. FIXED.

  4. BUG: When starting a new game the colors on the HiRes part of the
     gameboard are wrong. FIXED.

  5. BUG: Several of the new Sidewinder protracker mods won't work with
     the playroutine. They are playing EXTREMELY slowly. I converted
     them to MED MMD1 so this is NOW FIXED.

  6. MODIFIED the game so that if you turn off sound and speech then
     the music plays continuously through the spell-selection,
     spell-casting and movement phases of the game, only changing at
     the beginning of the next turn.

  7. INCLUDED CD advertisement for Sidewinder CDs into the docs.

  8. Color My World Modifications

  9. BUG: sometimes wizards cast Plasma Beam for some strange reason.
     then they always cast it up to the left, even if nothing is there,
     or even if it attacks multiple creatures that they own while not
     hurting any enemies.  Leaving this for SAI to investigate. Fixed
     by JC months later on October 20th, 1999. NOW FIXED.

 10. BUG in protracker play routine. There is a bug in the playroutine
     that causes certain protracker mods to play back incorrectly. It
     sounds like the notes are being played back about 100x too slowly.
     I have no idea how to debug this so I'm just converting the
     affected mods to MED format.  Converted LOTS of protracker mods to
     MED MMD1 format.

 11. NEEDED: Dear SAI, could you please adjust the loading and saving
     such that player 3 can save the game, and then when reloading the
     game it will reload to player 3's spell selection phase? Thanks.
     Implemented by JC in August 1999.

 12. OBSOLETED: EditPopupIDCMP is now handled my the main HandleIDCMP
     routine.  This means that "q" querying etc. now works properly in
     the editor.

 13. Temporarily turned off the end of turn confirmation as I find it
     annoying.

 14. Improved the implementation of the popup creature menus using an
     array of functions.

 15. Fixed a bug in ClearBoard().

 16. End Turn Confirmation is now an option in the menus. Default is
     OFF.

 17. PROBLEM: The "about" screen with the pentagrams hashes sometimes.
     It hashes a lot and looks utterly terrible under heavy CPU load.
     NOW FIXED by increasing the taskpri to 100 during the doublebuffer
     switching.

 18. PROBLEM: The credits scrolling is not 100% smooth and is very
     jerky under heavy CPU load. NOW FIXED by increasing taskpri to 100
     during the doublebuffer switching.

 19. NEGATIVE SCORE BUG: I played a game against JJ and I won but my
     score was negative and his was positive so he claimed he was
     really the winner. In the current version of the game shooting the
     following scrolls gives the following points. Scrolls of creatures
     award as many points as the original life of the real creature.
     moveit -124 Pox shield -125 acid rain -123 devastation -1 touch of
     god -116 ball lightning -114 plasma beam -113 sword of sassenrath
     -118 cursed sword -110 nomount -86. Other scrolls have various
     (mostly HUGE) positive scores associated with them. This is all
     caused by bad subscript errors. Points are awarded according to
     the .Life statistic. But Magic Spells don't have a .Life statistic
     so it just accesses some other data. Made required changes to
     DevastationHandler() also. DONE AND FIXED.

 20. BUG: DeathBringer struck a scroll dead. NOW FIXED.

 21. PROBLEM: We keep getting Emails from NTSC users who don't know how
     to PALboot their Amiga. I added in the AmigaToPAL cli command
     which requires OS 2.04 or higher. Now the game automatically puts
     the computer into pal mode. FIXED.

 22. BUG: Pressing 'q' on the creatures on the alt-o menu thing shows
     the spell description instead of their stats. NOW FIXED.

 23. Spell-List Editor Upgrade 0. Have a seperate spell-list editor
     which is different from the "board editor" 1. Its easy. Just make
     a SpellBoard for storing the spell list onto. DONE. 2. You select
     "Edit Spell List" from the Main Menu. DONE. 3. Figure out where
     the code goes when you select "Edit Spell List" ??? DONE. 4.
     delete copy and paste work exactly the same as in the
     board-editor. DONE. 5. Modify HandleIDCMP + make new menu. DONE. 6.
     Need CopySpellsFromListToBoard(player) (do this once at the
     beginning + anytime the player number is changed) DONE. 7. Need
     CopySpellsFromBoardToList(player) (do this whenever you select
     "quit" or change player number) DONE. 8. Need alt-i for "insert"
     an empty space into the spell-list. DONE. 9. Need alt-d to delete
     just as in the board editor unless it is used on an empty cell in
     which case the empty cell is deleted and all cells to the right
     are scooted 1 space to the left. DONE.

 24. Gamesave Format Upgrade: currentPlayer is now saved. BUG:
     ExorcistID is listed in the translation table twice! FIXED. BUG:
     Probability information was not completely saved. FIXED. BUG: the
     currentSpell was being saved but not translated. FIXED. BUG: When
     you save the game it resets back to player 1's turn. FIXED. BUG:
     When you load a game it resets back to player 1's turn. FIXED.
     REMOVED old stuff that is no longer needed.

 25. BUG: The FavoriteFoodID and RunsAwayFromID is not translated like
     all the other ids. So the first time we add a new spell to the
     game, all our previously designed levels will have creatures with
     messed up tastes and fears. NOW FIXED.

 26. HOPEFULLY I can now do a complete major upgrade or 2 or 3 and not
     have to convert all the old levels up to the new format.

 27. Line of Sight Upgrade. BUG: If you are trying to cast a roper or
     bolter wall etc. along a 45° angle, the "l" key will show that
     you have line of sight but sometimes the "c" key says you don't!
     And when the "c" says you can't cast it there you really can't
     cast it there even though it is in range and you have line of
     sight! This is caused by a problem in isLineOfSight. isLineOfSight
     @{i}SHOULD@{ui} work perfectly but it doesn't. I don't know why. Its like
     it is off by 1 or something. This problem only occurs when there
     are generators adjacent to the 45° path. If you want to
     investigate this mystery then please do so. In the meantime I have
     solved the problem by replacing all occurrences of isLineOfSight C
     code with isLineOfSightQ asm code. NOW FIXED.

 28. SPEEDUP: Computer controlled shooters now decide who they will
     shoot over 2x as fast as before!

 29. SPEEDUP: Computer AI is now MUCH faster than before!

 30. SPEEDUP: "c" key is now over 3x as fast as before!

 31. SPEEDUP: "s" key is now much faster!

 32. BUG: isLineOfSightQ does not automatically return TRUE when the
     source cell is the destination cell. (This prevented me from
     casting Combat on myself) NOW FIXED.

 33. FIXED various bugs with the Mass Ressurrect spell + pox or
     reincarnation or vanquished foes. It was all very broken. NOW
     FIXED.

 34. ALL files 100% cleaned up!

 35. Played a test game. Saved and Loaded multiple times. Everything
     works.

 36. REGISTERED USER on September 17th: a nice chap from Ireland mailed
     in his registration fee. He has an AGA Amiga 1200 tower with Zorro
     IV Busboard, Picasso IV gfx card, 50 Mhz 060, 64 Megs of RAM,
     Power Flyer, etc.

 37. Added Sidewinder to the Scrolling Credits.

 38. Played Sean's Levels 1-4 and 10. Added turns_left to the about
     screen.

 39. Added Registered_Text to hold the registered user's name.


