Improvements from 2.1 to 2.2
----------------------------

  1. The spell selection by computer players was notably slower on the
     A500 (this is your new regime of spell selection). However, the
     real problem here was that there was not enough on screen
     indication of what was happening. NOW FIXED

  2. Somehow there was a sleeping neo-otuygh which was not redrawn.

  3. Somehow there was a sleeping ogre-mage that was still animated.

  4. The team scores were still not correctly sorted.

  5. Several times players shot there own "hidden horrors" to reveal
     the red dragon. I think the probability of the hidden horror needs
     to be reduced below that of the red dragon. NOW FIXED

  6. The game locks up on the A500 when starting a new game after the
     completion on the previous game. The only seems to happen when
     there are lots of wizards. It can also be avoided by starting a
     new game from the menu before the game ends naturally. I am
     assuming that this situation is because memory is tight. NOW FIXED

  7. The teleport explode effect is applied to the wrong player. NOW
     FIXED

  8. The boil explode effect is applied to fire rather than water. NOW
     FIXED

  9. The initial set up was the same every time the program was loaded.
     NOW FIXED

 10. If you set the number of turns to "n" you actually get "n+1"
     turns. NOW FIXED

 11. Computer wizards and not conforming to the rules regarding the
     necropotence spell and discard spell. NOW FIXED

 12. Dad pressed the end-turn gadget in an attempt to cancel a spell.
     Instead it tried to cast the creature to some location off the
     bottom of the screen.  NOW FIXED (end of turn ghosted during
     casting)

 13. There is insufficient information given to the player indicating
     the pick up of a scroll. NOW FIXED (there is a text message and an
     audio effect)

 14. Casting Biohazard gave all scrolls recovery -1 and they
     subsequently all died in the next round. NOW ALLEGEDLY FIXED

 15. Flying creatures still show wings cursor even when engaged. NOW
     FIXED

 16. I cast a Meddle causing the nightmare I was mounted to become a
     skeleton (i.e. I should now have been mounted on a skeleton); but
     when I moved the skeleton my wizard was not moved. I think this
     means I need to check the "mounted" bit carefully when doing
     reincarnation. ALLEGEDLY FIXED

 17. Glen pointed out that the archery spell description does not
     actually say what the spell does, although he guessed correctly.
     NOW FIXED.

 18. Callum wanted "RETURN" to mean end-of-turn. NOW FIXED

 19. Callum suggested the right hand set of bars on the info pages be
     labelled "Recovery" at the top. NOW FIXED

 20. Fixed a bug with Repulsion which could leave the colours
     permanently screwed up.

 21. Made isStupidCast compliant with agent casting.

 22. Made menu option for script font on info screens.

 23. Made menu option for agent casting.

 24. Stopped the computer from moved onto nuked squares. Allowed
