Known bugs
==========

   Chaos has been extensively tested with @{b}Enforcer@{ub}, @{b}MuForce@{ub}, @{b}Mungwall@{ub}
and @{b}MuGuardianAngel@{ub} and in our experience does nothing nasty. However,
crashes may happen, if they do it is most helpful to me if you can note
carefully what was happening when the crash occurred.  There are a few
less serious bugs within the game which may be fixed in the future.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Reinstatement Bug@{ui}: When Dark Power, Vengeance, Decree, or
     Justice succeeds in killing a creature upon a corpse, the creature
     is killed but the corpse is brought back to life. This "bug" is
     deliberately incorporated in the program. Advanced players will
     exploit this fact in the obvious way.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Cat Lord@{ui}: Theoretically there should only ever be one Cat Lord.
     However, it possible to create more than one by a variety of
     methods:

       a. using Alter Reality,

       b. using Mutate,

       c. by waking a sleeping one,

       d. by raising a dead one,

       e. using Request.

     Multiple Cat Lords will not cause the game to crash but may result
     in cats changing sides several times, moving multiple times, and
     other undocumented effects. We leave it to you to explore the
     possibilities.

   @{b}*@{ub}     @{i}Classic Bugs@{ui}: The classic mode is not perfect and it is
     possible that spells not normally available will occur. Known
     cases are the faun casting sleep. The thundermare and iridium
     powerups are still possible. If generators are used then the
     bipedal generator will still generate creatures not normally
     available in classic mode.


